At WorkFusion, we build software that is changing the world and transforming workplaces. Our technology automates repetitive, data-intensive work so people can be freed from the mundane to pursue the meaningful, companies can grow further, and customers can be served faster and better. 
 
WorkFusion is increasingly recognized as the world leader in industry-specific process automation, offering AI-powered software with particular focus on the needs of banking, financial services, and insurance enterprises. Our Intelligent Automation Cloud combines RPA, machine learning and analytics in one unrivaled platform that can be deployed quickly and scale without limit. We compete in the worldâ€™s fastest-growing software segment and we are growing at record pace with customers spanning the globe. 
 
As the health and safety of our teams is always a primary concern, we are currently a primarily remote workforce worldwide. Officially, our headquarters is in New York City (on Wall Street) with additional hubs in Canada, Europe and Asia. 
Position 
WorkFusion is seeking an Automation Consultant to join the Customer Success team with one of the world's leading and fastest growing artificial intelligence and robotics technology companies. 
 
Successful candidates will have a combination of top tier consulting, technology and relevant industry experience. They will be responsible for leading clients and technology partners on strategic and transformational initiatives relevant to Automation, including project and program definition/execution, in a fast-paced environment to drive top-line revenue growth and efficiency/cost savings, improve operational performance and enhance client experience across WorkFusionâ€™s portfolio of clients.
 Some travel (once safe) required due to the global nature of the business and customer base.
 Key responsibilities Conduct consulting engagements based on enablement materials as part of our Client and Partnersâ€™ transformation programs Structure and execute on initiatives by developing work plans, gathering and synthesizing relevant data, leading analyses, developing final recommendations and creating execution roadmap Conduct rapid diagnostic and/or detailed due diligence to articulate opportunity impact, timing and other parameters Build business cases for strategic programs and present or support presentations to senior management to achieve executive level buy-in Program management and coordination of strategic initiatives Collaborate with Business Transformation team members, WorkFusion leaders and subject matter experts on sales enablement and engagement materials relevant to our Clients and Partners Communicate results with executive leadership and broader organization Manage deadlines / timeframes, proactively escalating issues as needed Translate business requirements into automation solution designs 
